1
00:00:40,289 --> 00:00:57,123
THE TALL BLOND GUY WITH ONE BLACK SHOE

2
00:02:20,713 --> 00:02:24,505
Somewhere in New York...

3
00:02:31,230 --> 00:02:35,189
You were arrested at customs in New York...

4
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:39,189
...trying to get through with a car
containing 40 kilos of heroin. Do you confess?

5
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:42,620
Yes. I've asked for
a lie detector test.

6
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:46,108
Because I'm telling the truth.

7
00:02:46,710 --> 00:02:49,702
And you say that you're not...

8
00:02:50,230 --> 00:02:53,302
...a drug trafficker?
- No, I'm not.

9
00:02:57,230 --> 00:03:01,985
Whom are you working for?
- The counter intelligence of my country.

10
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:06,182
I came from the USA on a mission.
I'm not a drug trafficker.

11
00:03:06,230 --> 00:03:09,302
What kind of mission?

12
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:14,669
The head of my service told me
to get the drugs to the USA.

13
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:18,100
He should be held responsible
for the matter.

14
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:21,270
I'm innocent.

15
00:03:24,798 --> 00:03:28,295
Somewhere in Paris...

16
00:03:34,030 --> 00:03:36,624
Yes. Come in.

17
00:03:43,230 --> 00:03:46,222
Back from holidays already, sir?

18
00:03:46,950 --> 00:03:49,544
Sit down.

19
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:55,420
What's this mess, dear Bernard?

20
00:03:57,230 --> 00:04:00,506
I'm more surprised than anybody, sir.
- Really?

21
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:04,100
Yes. I found out through the press.
I'm astonished.

22
00:04:06,230 --> 00:04:10,189
Somebody's making a fool of me.
It's nasty.

23
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:13,302
Very nasty, sir.
- This trafficker pretends...

24
00:04:14,230 --> 00:04:18,985
...he's working for me, but he isn't.
- He's not working for me either.

25
00:04:19,030 --> 00:04:22,420
Well for whom does he work then?
- I don't know, sir.

26
00:04:26,709 --> 00:04:30,622
This situation could cost
me my job. You will...

27
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:35,188
...succeed me as head of the service.
- No matter who'll succeed you...

28
00:04:35,229 --> 00:04:38,619
...I'm sure he'll try
to follow in your footsteps.

29
00:04:39,229 --> 00:04:42,221
With the same goals and energy.

30
00:04:43,229 --> 00:04:46,107
Thank you, dear Bernard.

31
00:04:48,709 --> 00:04:51,781
Have you ever seen this
trafficker?

32
00:04:52,710 --> 00:04:55,224
Never, sir.

33
00:04:56,829 --> 00:04:59,423
It's a fake!

34
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:06,588
A fake? That's possible.

35
00:05:07,109 --> 00:05:10,499
Bloody well done then,
but it's possible.

36
00:05:22,229 --> 00:05:26,142
Alright... that was all.
You can go to work.

37
00:05:26,229 --> 00:05:28,026
Bernard.

38
00:05:39,309 --> 00:05:41,106
Bernard?

39
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:43,666
Yes, sir?

40
00:05:43,709 --> 00:05:46,701
Did you receive my case of wine?

41
00:05:47,229 --> 00:05:50,221
Yes, I wanted to thank you.

42
00:05:51,710 --> 00:05:54,702
You shouldn't have...
- I said to myself:

43
00:05:56,749 --> 00:06:00,139
What's a good present to
give to Saint Bernard?

44
00:06:02,749 --> 00:06:05,821
First I thought of a cask of rum.

45
00:06:06,789 --> 00:06:09,861
And then I remembered
that our friend Milan...

46
00:06:10,349 --> 00:06:14,262
...loves good wine.
- But a case of Mouton-Rothschild!

47
00:06:15,629 --> 00:06:18,621
And from 1970.
- It's excellent.

48
00:06:19,549 --> 00:06:23,986
Store it in a good cellar and
drink it to my health in ten years.

49
00:06:24,829 --> 00:06:28,105
I hope we'll drink it together, sir.

50
00:06:32,069 --> 00:06:34,060
Why not?

51
00:06:52,230 --> 00:06:54,824
Yes, sir.

52
00:06:58,629 --> 00:07:01,507
The thing with the car failed.

53
00:07:07,429 --> 00:07:10,819
I didn't find dear Bernard
in very good shape.

54
00:07:11,429 --> 00:07:14,705
No, not very.
- He should take a holiday.

55
00:07:15,429 --> 00:07:19,866
Come in, dear Perrache.
- He just arrived home, sir.

56
00:07:20,789 --> 00:07:24,782
Excuse me, sir. How was
your holiday, sir?

57
00:07:25,549 --> 00:07:28,621
It was a good holiday, Perrache.
Very good.

58
00:07:29,229 --> 00:07:32,301
Very quiet.
We had a good rest.

59
00:07:33,229 --> 00:07:36,221
Mother came back in great shape.

60
00:07:37,229 --> 00:07:40,301
A cure of 10 days makes her
10 years younger.

61
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:44,582
We didn't have great weather, but
the climate is very invigorating.

62
00:07:44,629 --> 00:07:48,019
When we came back to Paris,
we felt like we were suffocating.

63
00:07:49,229 --> 00:07:52,505
The cure is mainly about
fresh air.

64
00:07:53,229 --> 00:07:57,188
There is no pollution yet
in the Puy-de-Dôme.

65
00:07:57,229 --> 00:08:00,619
It was nice. And the mud
baths were marvellous.

66
00:08:02,229 --> 00:08:06,142
Hot mud really relaxes the nerves.

67
00:08:06,229 --> 00:08:09,619
And afterwards they put you
under ice cold water.

68
00:08:13,709 --> 00:08:17,668
He's also bugging your apartment.
A car full of drugs...

69
00:08:17,710 --> 00:08:21,100
...microphones in the statues.
Milan doesn't stop at anything.

70
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:26,180
He's behind the affair with the car,
but I can't prove it.

71
00:08:26,229 --> 00:08:29,505
I discovered the microphones
by coincidence.

72
00:08:29,710 --> 00:08:32,588
It was well done.

73
00:08:33,709 --> 00:08:37,099
He's working hard for it.
- I hate careerists.

74
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:41,140
They never get very far.
- We should remind him that...

75
00:08:41,950 --> 00:08:44,942
...it's not his job to do
what he can to replace...

76
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:50,143
...you as the head of the service.

77
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:53,506
Why the microphones?
- Milan played a dirty trick on me...

78
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:58,189
...and he's expecting me to hit back.
It is fun to imagine him...

79
00:08:58,230 --> 00:09:01,506
...trembling with fear behind
his phone tapping equipment.

80
00:09:04,229 --> 00:09:07,619
He should keep that on.
He'll catch a cold.

81
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:11,108
Milan deserves to be
taught a lesson.

82
00:09:12,230 --> 00:09:16,189
I don't want an assistant who confuses
intelligence with dirty games.

83
00:09:16,229 --> 00:09:19,619
The best duck pâté
I've ever had.

84
00:09:20,230 --> 00:09:24,189
Mother had three servings.
She wouldn't listen to reason.

85
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:29,224
I told her: "Mother, you're going
to be sick".

86
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:34,620
But, dear Perrache, I didn't
make you come here...

87
00:09:35,230 --> 00:09:38,222
...to tell you about my holiday.

88
00:09:39,230 --> 00:09:43,143
Tomorrow morning, at 9:30,
a man arrives at Orly.

89
00:09:43,230 --> 00:09:46,620
This man should be able to help us
quickly clear up...

90
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:51,143
...this dirty American mess.
You have to look after him.

91
00:09:51,230 --> 00:09:53,186
Alright, sir.

92
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:56,620
I hope we can keep the service
out of this affair.

93
00:09:57,230 --> 00:10:00,620
Of course, sir.
- This man will need protection.

94
00:10:01,230 --> 00:10:04,620
Make sure he's safe
and take Poucet and Chaperon with you.

95
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:08,222
I have faith in them.
- Yes, sir.

96
00:10:09,230 --> 00:10:13,143
Nine thirty at the airport.
Don't be late, Perrache,

97
00:10:13,230 --> 00:10:16,302
It's important.
And a big secret.

98
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:20,620
Understood, sir.
- Do you like Italian food?

99
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:22,709
What?

100
00:10:28,029 --> 00:10:31,101
Tomorrow morning, at Orly,
at nine thirty...

101
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:35,420
This man should be able to help us
quickly clear up...

102
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:39,625
...this dirty American mess.
- Damn!

103
00:10:41,230 --> 00:10:44,302
The guy we're meeting...
Who is it?

104
00:10:45,230 --> 00:10:48,108
I don't know
- Excuse me?

105
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:52,667
I don't know. Go to Orly, tomorrow
at nine thirty and pick a man.

106
00:10:52,710 --> 00:10:56,100
I don't understand.
- Yes, pick one. Choose anybody.

107
00:10:56,710 --> 00:10:59,986
A man from the crowd.
As anonymous as possible.

108
00:11:00,710 --> 00:11:03,908
It doesn't matter at all
who you'll pick.

109
00:11:04,108 --> 00:11:05,138
It's make believe.

110
00:11:06,151 --> 00:11:09,010
What matters is that
Milan takes the bait.

111
00:11:11,685 --> 00:11:19,860
I'll tell you what you'll be looking for
at the airport, dear Perrache:

112
00:11:19,910 --> 00:11:22,902
...an asshole trap!

113
00:11:27,230 --> 00:11:30,222
Who is this guy we have to protect?

114
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:35,106
Well? Who is it?
- You don't need to know.

115
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:40,623
Follow him discretely.
He can't notice a thing.

116
00:12:13,710 --> 00:12:16,702
Arrival from Sydney.

117
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:20,222
Flight Air France nr 704, gate 17.

118
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:23,668
Is your guy from Australia?

119
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:27,100
Arrival from Sydney,
Air France flight 704, gate 17.

120
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:32,224
Choose anybody...

121
00:12:34,310 --> 00:12:37,188
...a man from the crowd...

122
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:40,108
...as anonymous as possible...

123
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:44,024
Choose.

124
00:12:44,710 --> 00:12:47,304
It's make believe...

125
00:12:48,230 --> 00:12:50,824
Choose.

126
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:56,983
Is he from Australia?
- No.

127
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:02,908
It's nine thirty.

128
00:13:11,710 --> 00:13:14,702
Arrival from Munich...

129
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:17,824
He's from Munich.

130
00:13:19,350 --> 00:13:22,740
Arrival from Munich,
Lufthansa flight 320, gate 12.

131
00:13:27,630 --> 00:13:30,224
Is he a musician?

132
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:35,384
Is that him?
- No.

133
00:13:35,430 --> 00:13:38,308
Maybe he missed the plane.

134
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:48,344
He'll be there.

135
00:13:53,350 --> 00:13:55,944
Is he black?

136
00:14:13,710 --> 00:14:15,507
That's him.

137
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:24,942
A tall blond guy with a black shoe.

138
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:31,707
Michel!

139
00:14:41,230 --> 00:14:44,222
Excuse me, sir. I made a mistake.

140
00:15:36,390 --> 00:15:39,223
François Perrin, 32 years old, single.

141
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:49,624
Violinist. Lives at 24 Rue de I'Alouette,
7th arrondissement. Arrived from Munich.

142
00:15:53,510 --> 00:15:56,582
There's no file about him?
- No, sir.

143
00:15:57,550 --> 00:16:01,543
Not with the intelligence service,
not with Internal Affairs.

144
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:38,742
He made a phone call from the airport.
- To whom?

145
00:16:39,270 --> 00:16:42,262
To his dentist.
- And the violin case?

146
00:16:46,230 --> 00:16:50,223
I want to know tomorrow who
he is and what he's going to do.

147
00:16:50,270 --> 00:16:53,660
That's not a lot of time. 24 hours.
- It's all the time we have.

148
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:57,620
We have to neutralise him right away.
- Do we kill him?

149
00:16:58,230 --> 00:17:02,189
I want to know what he's up to.
Go to work.

150
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:06,189
Do what it takes. Discretely.
We don't want to get caught.

151
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:09,302
Poucet and Chaperon don't know you.

152
00:17:10,229 --> 00:17:13,107
Alright, sir.
- Botrel!

153
00:17:17,230 --> 00:17:19,949
Why a black shoe?

154
00:17:31,949 --> 00:17:35,339
Why a violinist?
- You said to pick anybody.

155
00:17:36,349 --> 00:17:39,341
Yes, but why a violinist?

156
00:17:39,869 --> 00:17:42,861
Because he had a black shoe.

157
00:17:53,629 --> 00:17:56,507
Hello! Hello! Hello!

158
00:17:56,629 --> 00:18:00,542
What? Who's speaking?
- Its doctor Müller from Munich.

159
00:18:01,229 --> 00:18:05,188
You're a murderer, a butcher.
You executed him in a terrible way.

160
00:18:05,229 --> 00:18:08,221
Poor Prokofiev!

161
00:18:09,229 --> 00:18:13,188
Maurice, don't be an asshole.
I'm soaking, just out of the bath.

162
00:18:13,229 --> 00:18:16,665
You didn't recognise me, idiot.
Do we still meet at 4?

163
00:18:16,710 --> 00:18:20,669
Listen, Maurice, I lost a filling
at the airport. My tooth hurts.

164
00:18:20,709 --> 00:18:24,668
Whatever, I'll be there at 4.
- I swear. I called the dentist.

165
00:18:24,709 --> 00:18:28,668
Doctor Michaux can't see me until
tomorrow morning. And it hurts.

166
00:18:28,710 --> 00:18:31,986
Alright, see you at 4.
- But...

167
00:18:38,989 --> 00:18:43,187
Keep listening. Don't miss it
when Toulouse contacts him.

168
00:18:43,229 --> 00:18:46,619
Alright, sir.
- We have to make him leave the house.

169
00:18:47,349 --> 00:18:50,421
What's the name of the dentist?
- Michaux.

170
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:54,188
It's Mr. Perrin.
- Keep it open. What?

171
00:18:54,229 --> 00:18:58,142
He says he's suffering badly.
- Keep it open. Alright, listen...

172
00:18:58,229 --> 00:19:02,222
I'll do him in between.
Tell him to come in an hour.

173
00:19:03,230 --> 00:19:05,061
Keep it open.

174
00:19:05,229 --> 00:19:08,346
In an hour? Perfect.

175
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:17,822
Hello?

176
00:19:18,229 --> 00:19:22,142
Hello? This is Dr Michaux's practice.
The doctor can see you...

177
00:19:22,709 --> 00:19:27,146
...in an hour if that suits you.
- Alright. Well, that's great.

178
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:31,189
That's very friendly. thank you.
It's hurting a bit less.

179
00:19:31,229 --> 00:19:33,618
But I'll be there in an hour.

180
00:19:33,669 --> 00:19:36,308
He changed shoes.

181
00:19:44,629 --> 00:19:48,019
He changed shoes.
Renault 15, orange red.

182
00:19:48,629 --> 00:19:51,507
Number plate 2868 X 075.

183
00:22:41,469 --> 00:22:44,541
Hello?
He's not going to the dentist.

184
00:22:50,629 --> 00:22:53,507
He's not going to the dentist.

185
00:23:06,069 --> 00:23:08,663
Hello, sir.

186
00:23:08,709 --> 00:23:11,667
He's not going to the dentist.
- Why not?

187
00:23:11,709 --> 00:23:15,622
I don't know, sir.
- Why isn't he going to the dentist?

188
00:23:15,710 --> 00:23:18,668
Why not?
- He's going to the park.

189
00:23:18,709 --> 00:23:22,099
Excuse me, sir, what?
- He's going to the park.

190
00:23:22,709 --> 00:23:25,143
He's going to the park...

191
00:23:33,629 --> 00:23:36,223
He's going on the lake.

192
00:23:38,229 --> 00:23:41,904
He's renting a boat.
- What's he doing on the lake?

193
00:23:41,949 --> 00:23:46,784
Yes, what's he doing on the lake?
- He must have noticed us. No problem.

194
00:23:47,229 --> 00:23:51,142
We'll wait for him at the dentist's.
What's he doing on the lake?

195
00:23:54,709 --> 00:23:56,506
He's rowing.

196
00:23:57,829 --> 00:24:01,822
Ah, yes. He's rowing.
- Rowing. - Rowing.

197
00:24:05,269 --> 00:24:09,262
Not too close. Go to the island.
- I'm hot.

198
00:24:10,349 --> 00:24:13,341
He's on the island.
In the restaurant.

199
00:24:18,069 --> 00:24:21,061
He's throwing bread at the ducks?
Damn.

200
00:24:37,029 --> 00:24:41,022
Hello, can you hear me?
Hello, can you hear me?

201
00:24:41,229 --> 00:24:43,823
5, 4, 3, 2, 1, 0.

202
00:24:47,069 --> 00:24:50,857
I can hear you fine.
Hurry. He's finished lunch.

203
00:24:56,229 --> 00:25:00,188
They made him leave his place
and they're bugging the apartment.

204
00:25:00,229 --> 00:25:04,188
They must be finished by now.
Milan took the bait.

205
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:08,189
He brought all his men.
- Our little plan has already shown us...

206
00:25:08,229 --> 00:25:12,302
...who are in Milan's secret team.
That's good, isn't it?

207
00:25:12,349 --> 00:25:17,184
There are too many people I don't
know in my own service.

208
00:25:17,749 --> 00:25:21,662
Alright. You can go have lunch.
- There was a black guy at Orly...

209
00:25:22,629 --> 00:25:26,019
A big black guy wearing a woollen coat.
I picked a tall blond guy...

210
00:25:26,669 --> 00:25:30,059
...with a black shoe over a tall
black guy with a green woollen coat.

211
00:25:32,629 --> 00:25:37,703
Listen, old man, if you want to produce
literature, wait until after you're retired.

212
00:25:38,869 --> 00:25:41,463
Enjoy your lunch.

213
00:25:49,549 --> 00:25:52,621
Won't you finish your leaks,
Louis?

214
00:25:52,789 --> 00:25:55,383
No, thanks, mother.

215
00:25:57,709 --> 00:26:00,701
Yesterday was Bernard Milan's birthday.

216
00:26:01,469 --> 00:26:06,463
I hope you remembered?
- Yes, mother, I remembered.

217
00:26:07,629 --> 00:26:10,905
Born in Epinal, in the Vosges,
on 28 March 1940.

218
00:26:12,349 --> 00:26:15,739
Only son, late arrival...
His mother, Marie Bugeaud.

219
00:26:16,710 --> 00:26:19,588
45 years old, teacher.

220
00:26:19,749 --> 00:26:23,662
His father, Gérard Perrin, 55 years old,
teacher and amateur violinist.

221
00:26:26,629 --> 00:26:29,701
Two teachers, retirement
came quickly.

222
00:26:31,349 --> 00:26:35,786
Uneventful childhood.
His father introduced him to music.

223
00:26:39,710 --> 00:26:42,702
Practising catholic.
- Homosexual?

224
00:26:44,709 --> 00:26:48,099
No. Goes to the conservatory
of Strasbourg at the age of 13.

225
00:26:48,709 --> 00:26:51,985
Leaves at 15 to spend
a year at a sanatorium.

226
00:26:52,710 --> 00:26:56,100
Lost his virginity to the head nurse.
- How do you know?

227
00:26:56,709 --> 00:26:58,700
A letter.

228
00:26:58,749 --> 00:27:01,821
Relax, muffin, I'm not pregnant.

229
00:27:06,309 --> 00:27:09,699
Cured, he goes to the conservatory
of Paris. First price...

230
00:27:10,349 --> 00:27:15,423
28 months of military service.
Participates in none of the colonial wars.

231
00:27:15,830 --> 00:27:18,822
Serves his time in army bands.

232
00:27:18,869 --> 00:27:22,259
First violin in a string orchestra
for 5 years now.

233
00:27:22,709 --> 00:27:26,668
Often travels abroad.
Also to the USA.

234
00:27:26,710 --> 00:27:30,100
There! He worked in the USA.
I knew it.

235
00:27:30,709 --> 00:27:34,099
But none of our people know him.
- But of course.

236
00:27:35,469 --> 00:27:40,179
He's a super agent, working on his own.
