and he loves music.

409
00:45:17,709 --> 00:45:20,303
Six years is the right age, I think.

410
00:45:20,349 --> 00:45:23,341
I'd prefer lessons at home.

411
00:45:24,029 --> 00:45:26,623
He's so young.

412
00:45:26,710 --> 00:45:30,100
My father also collected
old instruments.

413
00:45:33,709 --> 00:45:36,587
He died last year.

414
00:45:37,229 --> 00:45:40,107
He left it all to me.
- I see.

415
00:45:42,029 --> 00:45:46,261
I don't know much about it but I
think some instruments are interesting.

416
00:45:46,309 --> 00:45:51,144
If you like, I can show you
when you come to the house.

417
00:45:53,229 --> 00:45:57,188
The little one's on holiday at the moment.
He won't be back until next week.

418
00:45:57,229 --> 00:46:00,301
I don't intend to keep the collection.

419
00:46:01,229 --> 00:46:04,346
Too many memories.

420
00:46:09,309 --> 00:46:11,106
I see.

421
00:46:12,269 --> 00:46:17,343
You could at least have a look.
But you'd have to be quick.

422
00:46:18,549 --> 00:46:21,143
When?
- Let's see...

423
00:46:21,229 --> 00:46:24,619
Tomorrow is impossible.
So is Wednesday.

424
00:46:25,229 --> 00:46:28,301
What are you doing this evening?
- Today?

425
00:46:30,069 --> 00:46:34,904
I invited a few friends.
Would you like to come over?

426
00:46:35,469 --> 00:46:38,461
This is my address: 85 Rue des Vignes.

427
00:46:44,789 --> 00:46:46,586
See you tonight.

428
00:46:51,389 --> 00:46:55,826
No, tonight's impossible.
